# Basic Wi-Fi Troubleshooting Steps

URL: https://www.electric.ai/blog/cant-connect-to-internet-how-to-troubleshoot

1. Check if Wi-Fi is enabled on your laptop.
2. Restart your laptop and router to reset any potential issues.
3. Forget the network and reconnect to it by selecting "Forget" and choosing it again from the list of available networks.
4. Make sure that the laptop is set to obtain an IP address automatically by checking the TCP/IP settings.
5. Update your network adapter drivers to ensure they're not outdated.
6. Run Windows Network Troubleshooter (Right-click on Wi-Fi icon > Troubleshoot problems).
